{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Grease a round springform cake tin (24 cm) and set aside.","Place onion into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add oil, cumin, cinnamon, ground coriander, fennel seeds and saffron and cook <nobr>3 min\/90°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add mince and cook <nobr>4 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Scrape down base and sides of mixing bowl with spatula, breaking up any lumps. Cook for a further <nobr>3 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add water, stock paste, 20 g of the pine nuts, dried apricots, sultanas (optional), lemon zest and juice and cook <nobr>5 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Transfer onto a plate and spread out to cool (approx. 10 minutes).","Preheat oven to 220°C.","Brush a sheet of filo pastry with oil. Line the springform tin with oiled pastry, allowing pastry to overlap the edge of the tin. Repeat with a second layer of filo pastry, positioning the corners so that a star shape is formed. Repeat with 3 more layers of filo pastry (using 5 sheets in total).","Place cooled mince mixture into tin. Fold in overhanging edges of pastry to enclose the filling. Brush remaining 3 sheets of filo pastry with oil, then crumple and place over top of pastilla. Transfer pastilla into oven and reduce temperature to 190°C. Bake for 20-25 minutes (190°C) or until crisp on top. Cool in tin for 10 minutes, then remove from tin and transfer onto a serving plate. Garnish with extra pine nuts and dust with cinnamon and icing sugar."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 brown onion, cut into halves","30 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing and brushing","2 tsp ground cumin","1 tbsp ground cinnamon, plus extra for dusting","2 tsp ground coriander","2 tsp fennel seeds","1 pinch saffron","500 g beef mince","80 g water","1 tsp Vegetable stock paste (see Tip)","20 g pine nuts, plus extra for garnishing","150 g dried apricots, cut into quarters","50 g sultanas              (optional)","1 lemon, zest and juice","8 sheet filo pastry","icing sugar, for dusting"]}],"id":"r214340","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-V8Z0Y6hFOlI\/XZQGulXZu1I\/AAAAAAAAcBM\/0WlO9p4H3dEdqMfOJ4BnNXvT-xGkBkfSwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_WfizLUSiWa9kgOSe.png","title":"Beef, apricot and pine nut pastilla","publishedAt":"2017-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"23.8 g","fat":"25 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"31.6 g","calories":"1915.8 kJ \/ 456.1 kcal"},"usefulItems":"springform cake tin (24 cm), pastry brush, plate, serving plate, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","Pastilla, also called bastilla, is a sweet and savoury spiced meat and apricot pie topped with a sugared crust."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 20m","6 portions"]}